HEADWORD: Crosswort
<hw>Cross"wort`</hw> <pr>(-w?rt`)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld>
<def>A name given to several inconspicuous plants having leaves in
whorls of four, as species of <xex>Crucianella</xex>,
<xex>Valantia</xex>, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>crotal</ent>⟦br⟧
